(Correction
    "Lists in NOTA are homogeneous — every element is the same type. A list of mixed-type tuples (e.g. [date time quote]) is not valid NOTA. Heterogeneous positional structures are records (wrapped type + positional fields). My three NOTA mistakes this session — labeled-field tables, superfluous Said wrappers, heterogeneous nested lists — all come from the same root: not having actually read NOTA's grammar. The skill skills/nota-design.md does not currently teach the homogeneous-list rule explicitly."
